  "version": "2",
  "title": "Preinfuse then 45ml of water",
  "author": "Decent",
  "notes": "Australian barista Matt Perger suggested this technique to us. The idea is to fully saturate your puck, and then squeeze the brewed coffee out using a calculated water volume.  This results in consistently brewed espresso without needing to use a scale.",
